<TITLE> CA cuts short his day's work </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 24 (bdnews24.com)Chief adviser Fakhruddin Ahmed could not join a programme set for Monday afternoon as he felt "unwell", an adviser said. The CA cut short his day's work schedule and went home. Fakhruddin had been scheduled to preside over the meetings of the National Economic Council and ECNEC at the NEC conference room at Sher-e-Bangla Nagar Monday but could not go there. Finance adviser AB Mirza Azizul Islam chaired the twin meetings. After the meeting, the finance adviser told reporters: "The chief adviser could not come to today's meetings as he felt unwell." The CA's press secretary Syed Fahim Munaim told bdnews24.com by phone: "The chief adviser has caught cold." Fakhruddin will join all programmes scheduled for Tuesday, including the Independence Award ceremony and a meeting of the council of advisers, Munaim said. bdnews24.c
